<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-558] AnyClass.class and AnyClass.getClass() always return java.lang.Class.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-558</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The following script demonstrates the problem.  The &quot;.class&quot; syntax and calls to getClass() on any class return the same result: java.lang.Class.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Script:&lt;br/&gt;
-------&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;System.out.println java.lang.String.class&lt;br/&gt;
System.out.println java.lang.String.getClass()&lt;br/&gt;
System.out.println java.util.LinkedList.class&lt;br/&gt;
System.out.println java.util.LinkedList.getClass()&lt;br/&gt;
System.out.println java.sql.Timestamp.class&lt;br/&gt;
System.out.println java.sql.Timestamp.getClass()&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Output:&lt;br/&gt;
-------&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;class java.lang.Class&lt;br/&gt;
class java.lang.Class&lt;br/&gt;
class java.lang.Class&lt;br/&gt;
class java.lang.Class&lt;br/&gt;
class java.lang.Class&lt;br/&gt;
class java.lang.Class&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This may be related to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-440&quot; title=&quot;.class doesn&amp;#39;t work on maps&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;GROOVY-440&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;GROOVY-440&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://jira.codehaus.org/browse/GROOVY-440&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://jira.codehaus.org/browse/GROOVY-440&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Windows XP, JDK 1.4, Groovy 6/25 snapshot build</environment>
